(12, 10402, 'Slough', 61, 'female', 'Fiona Mactaggart', 'http://www.theyworkforyou.com/images/mpsL/10402.jpeg', 'Intelligence and Security (Joint Committee)', '', 'Labour', 'Home Department, Work and Pensions, Health, Justice, Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, Public Appointments, Human Trafficking, Departmental Public Appointments, Action for Employment, Domestic Violence', '<div class=`regmemcategory`>8. Land and Property</div>\n<div class=`regmemitem`>Office premises in Glasgow (held on my behalf by trustees), from which rental income is received.</div>\n<div class=`regmemcategory`>9. Registrable shareholdings</div>\n<div class=`regmemitem`>(b) Mactaggart Heritable Holdings Ltd.; property investment and management.</div>\n<div class=`regmemcategory`>11. Miscellaneous</div>\n<div class=`regmemitem`><span style=`        color: 000000;       `>I have made an interest-free loan of&#160;&#163;17,000 to Slough Labour Memorial Hall, a registered friendly society, from whom I rent my constituency office. The loan is to pay for refurbishing other parts of the premises and replacing a boiler. &#163;12,000 has been repaid. </span><span style=`        color: 000000;       `><em>(Registered 26 January 2012; updated 19 March 2013, 5 June 2013, 23 August 2013 and 23 December 2013)</em></span></div>\n'),
